Module Frogger

Package p4_group_8_repo.Views

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    GameViews
    An interface for all the different views in the game.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    EndOfGame
    This class is responsible for what happens at the end of the game.
    EndScreenView
    This class is responsible for displaying the end screen at the end of the game which consists of the list of high scores in the game and a button to go back to the main menu.
    EndScreenViewTest
    Test for the EndScreenView class.
    GameScreenView
    This class is responsible for displaying the game screen view on which the user play the game.
    GameScreenViewTest
    Test for the GameScreenView class.
    HelpScreenView
    Creates the help screen through which the user can get an idea of how to play the game.
    HelpScreenViewTest
    Test for the HelpScreenView class.
    HighScoresMenuView
    Creates a menu that allows the user to select which level's high scores they want to view.
    HighScoresMenuViewTest
    Test for the HighScoresMenuView class.
    LevelsMenuView
    This class is responsible for displaying the Levels Menu in which the user can select a level from the 5 levels of the game to play.
    LevelsMenuViewTest
    Test for the LevelsMenuView class.
    MyStage
    MyStage class which extends the World class.
    MyStageTest
    Test for the MyStage class.
    ScoresData
    This class facilitates the fetching of data from the Scores file.
    StartScreenView
    This class is responsible for displaying the Start Screen which the user sees first upon clicking on the game.
    StartScreenViewTest
    Test for the StartScreenView class.
    World
    This class represents a 2D world in which the Actors of the game live.
